{
  "title": "Programming with C++",
  "html": "<main><header class=\"section-page-header\"><div class=\"row d-flex justify-content-between\"><div class=\"col col-sm-10\"></div><!----></div><!----><h1>Programming with C++</h1><p class=\"text-secondary mb-0\"> Information for programmers developing with Unreal Engine. </p><!----></header><!----><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-lg-9 print-w-100\"><div class=\"b-img\"><img class=\"unreal-doc-img\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Programming with C++\" width=\"1920\" height=\"335\" loading=\"lazy\" fetchpriority=\"auto\" decoding=\"auto\" ng-img=\"true\" src=\"https://dev.epicgames.com/community/api/documentation/image/eb56a71d-9159-4d5f-ae1e-b3f22d730f07?resizing_type=fill&amp;width=1920&amp;height=335\" srcset=\"https://dev.epicgames.com/community/api/documentation/image/eb56a71d-9159-4d5f-ae1e-b3f22d730f07?resizing_type=fill&amp;width=1920&amp;height=335 1x, https://dev.epicgames.com/community/api/documentation/image/eb56a71d-9159-4d5f-ae1e-b3f22d730f07?resizing_type=fill&amp;width=3840&amp;height=670 2x\"></div><!----><!----><!----><header class=\"document-header mb-3 d-lg-none d-print-none\"><content-nav class=\"content-nav is-collapsible\" ngh=\"6\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></content-nav></header><!----><article><!----><!----><div document-content-blocks-renderer=\"\" class=\"d-block\" ngh=\"10\"><div id=\"content-blocks-renderer\" class=\"content-blocks-renderer\"><block-switch-control class=\"block-switch-control\" ngh=\"7\"><!----></block-switch-control><block-switch-info class=\"block-switch-info\" ngh=\"8\"><!----></block-switch-info><blocks-renderer id=\"blocks-renderer\" ngh=\"9\"><!----><block-markdown ngh=\"2\"><div class=\"block-markdown\"><p>Unreal Engine provides a robust framework for C++ programmers to help bring their vision to life.</p>\n\n<block-callout-md callout-type=\"note\">\n<p>This section assumes that you have some experience with C++.</p>\n</block-callout-md>\n\n<p>This section covers several powerful features that you can use to accelerate your development workflows. You can learn about:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>Creating new <a href=\"#unreal-doc:gameplay-classes-in-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/gameplay-classes-in-unreal-engine\">Gameplay classes</a> in C++, and all changes will be reflected in the <a href=\"#unreal-doc:unreal-editor-interface\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/unreal-editor-interface\">Unreal Editor</a> after compiling with either <a href=\"/documentation/404\" data-pathname=\"/404\">Visual Studio</a> or XCode. Creating classes in Unreal Engine is similar to creating standard C++ classes, functions, and variables. These are defined using <a href=\"#unreal-doc:epic-cplusplus-coding-standard-for-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/epic-cplusplus-coding-standard-for-unreal-engine\">standard C++ syntax</a>.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Using the <a href=\"#unreal-doc:reflection-system-in-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/reflection-system-in-unreal-engine\">Unreal Reflection System</a> to encapsulate your classes with <a href=\"#unreal-doc:metadata-specifiers-in-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/metadata-specifiers-in-unreal-engine\">Metadata Property Specifier</a> macros that provide Editor functionality. Each class defines a template for a new Object or Actor.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a href=\"#unreal-doc:containers-in-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/containers-in-unreal-engine\">Containers in Unreal Engine</a> provide information on Class and Data Structure collections.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Using the <a href=\"#unreal-doc:programming-with-cpp-in-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/programming-with-cpp-in-unreal-engine\">Gameplay Architecture</a> to build your projects in Unreal Engine. The Gameplay Framework provides a hierarchy of Objects and Actors. These classes contain boilerplate variables and functions you can use when creating and designing interactive experiences.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Creating <a href=\"#unreal-doc:delegates-and-lambda-functions-in-unreal-engine\" data-pathname=\"/unreal-engine/delegates-and-lambda-functions-in-unreal-engine\">Delegates</a> to call member functions on C++ objects in a generic, type-safe way. You can dynamically bind a delegate to a member function of an arbitrary object, calling the function on the object at a future time, even if the caller does not know the object`s type.</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"sectiondirectory\">Section Directory</h2>\n\n<block-dir-item-md description=\"Information for programmers developing Objects to be used with Unreal Engine.\" href=\"#unreal-doc:reflection-system-in-unreal-engine\" page-name=\"Unreal Engine Reflection System\" topic-icon=\"https://d1iv7db44yhgxn.cloudfront.net/documentation/images/8735245a-631f-49e0-a3f0-0344fd2c33e7/ue4_icon.png\" type=\"role\"></block-dir-item-md>\n<block-dir-item-md description=\"Write maintainable code by adhering to established standards and best practices.\" href=\"#unreal-doc:epic-cplusplus-coding-standard-for-unreal-engine\" page-name=\"Coding Standard\" topic-icon=\"https://d1iv7db44yhgxn.cloudfront.net/documentation/images/0dfce352-6d33-4ecf-8da2-a90733b2d190/ue4_icon.png\" type=\"role\"></block-dir-item-md>\n<block-dir-item-md description=\"Information on Class and Data Structure collections in Unreal Engine.\" href=\"#unreal-doc:containers-in-unreal-engine\" page-name=\"Containers in Unreal Engine\" topic-icon=\"https://d1iv7db44yhgxn.cloudfront.net/documentation/images/5402e815-9d22-4ae1-8b5e-e04ef4cba733/ue4_icon.png\" type=\"role\"></block-dir-item-md>\n<block-dir-item-md description=\"Reference for creating and implementing gameplay classes.\" href=\"#unreal-doc:programming-with-cpp-in-unreal-engine\" page-name=\"Gameplay Architecture\" topic-icon=\"https://d1iv7db44yhgxn.cloudfront.net/documentation/images/61bbb5c9-64ce-41e0-8509-707d85e07bdf/ue4_icon.png\" type=\"role\"></block-dir-item-md>\n<block-dir-item-md description=\"Data types that reference and execute member functions on C++ Objects\" href=\"#unreal-doc:delegates-and-lambda-functions-in-unreal-engine\" page-name=\"Delegates\" topic-icon=\"https://d1iv7db44yhgxn.cloudfront.net/documentation/images/6b082e41-a08c-4486-b4f3-bf7542993b73/ue4_icon.png\" type=\"role\"></block-dir-item-md>\n</div></block-markdown><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></blocks-renderer></div><!----></div></article><tags-list class=\"mt-1 d-print-none\" ngh=\"11\"><!----><ul class=\"labels-list is-links\"><li class=\"labels-item\"><!----><a class=\"labels-link\" href=\"/community/search?query=programming\"> programming</a><!----></li><!----></ul><!----></tags-list><!----><div class=\"col-lg-3 d-none d-lg-block d-print-none\"><!----></div></div><!----><!----><!----></main>",
